◆ event_trace_add_tracer()

int event_trace_add_tracer ( struct dentry *  parent,
struct trace_array *  tr 
)

event_trace_add_tracer - add a instance of a trace_array to events : The parent dentry to place the files/directories for events in : The trace array associated with these events

When a new instance is created, it needs to set up its events directory, as well as other files associated with events. It also creates the event hierachry in the /events directory.

Returns 0 on success.

Must be called with event_mutex held.

◆ trace_set_clr_event()

int trace_set_clr_event ( const char *  system,
const char *  event,
int  set 
)

trace_set_clr_event - enable or disable an event : system name to match (NULL for any system) : event name to match (NULL for all events, within system) : 1 to enable, 0 to disable

This is a way for other parts of the kernel to enable or disable event recording.

Returns 0 on success, -EINVAL if the parameters do not match any registered events.
